            <span>Rules</span> American football is played on a rectangular field that is 120 yards long and 53 ⅓ yards wide. Each team has 11 players on the field at a time. But teams can substitute for any or all of their players. The teams are divided
            into three roles: the offense, the defense and the special teams. A standard football game is made up of four 15-minute quarters; with a half-time intermission after the second quarter. If the offense fails to gain a first down (10 yards)
            after 4 downs, the team would lose possession of the ball. There are two ways to advance the ball: rushing and by throwing to the ball to a teammate. The offense team has possession of the ball if the team with the ball gets the ball stolen,
