            <br> 2. A field goal is worth 3 points, and it is scored by kicking the ball over the crossbar and through the goalposts.
            <br> 3. A safety is worth 2 points. It is scored by the defense when the offensive player in the possession of the ball is forced back into his own end zone and is tackled there, fumbles the ball out of the end zone, or commits intentional
